.TH "utf16_le_to_7bit" 9 "utf16_le_to_7bit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
utf16_le_to_7bit \- Naively converts a UTF-16LE string to 7-bit ASCII characters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" utf16_le_to_7bit
.BI "(const __le16 *in "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ","
.BI "u8 *out "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "in" 12
input UTF-16LE string
.IP "size" 12
size of the input string
.IP "out" 12
output string ptr, should be capable to store \fIsize\fP+1 characters
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Converts \fIsize\fP UTF16-LE symbols from \fIin\fP string to 7-bit
ASCII characters and stores them to \fIout\fP. Adds trailing zero to \fIout\fP array.
